sec.p:
The Manifesto was based on five assumptions:


that Muslims in Britain have to accept neither subservience as their inevitable and permanent condition nor the disintegration of their identity, culture and religion;

that, despite being a minority, Muslims here can define and pursue goals compatible with the goals of the global Ummah, the world community of Muslims, of which they are an integral part;

that Muslims in Britain need to create institutions and mobilise resources in pursuit of these goals;

that for Muslims this is also the only way to secure an honourable place in the wider British society;

that the option of ‘integration’ and/or ‘assimilation’ that is on offer as official policy in Britain must be firmly resisted and rejected. (ibid., 2)
